  <scopecontent id="aspace_e1f7e7dee07b55caa4ce63410116ae63">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Contains out-takes of "In the Year of the Pig," a film about the Vietnam War that includes French-era, combat, and rare Ho Chi Minh footage, dating between 1964 to 1968.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_f22157bee3a8f41c00d296c22c0817eb">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
<p>Emile DeAntonio, Collector.  In the Year of the Pig, #7038.  Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <bioghist id="aspace_8eb6fef9170353f69b712a4da54789e8">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Emile DeAntonio was born in Scranton, Pennsylvania, and graduated from Harvard University in 1940. After serving in World War II he began making films; the first to achieve notice was "Point of Order" a documentary/compilation concerning the McCarthy hearings of the early 1950's. He continued in that genre through "In the Year of the Pig.".</p>  </bioghist>
